                                pacmdvolume
                                ===========

             Copyright 2010-2013 Beat KÃ¼ng <beat-kueng@gmx.net>


pacmdvolume is a command line tool to control the PulseAudio sound server. It
shows sinks, sources, connected clients and controls their volume. It allows to
change each channel's volume separately. This is useful especially for surround
systems and the usage in scripts.


== compilation ==

requirements: 
	- pulseaudio (+ development files: debian/ubuntu package: libpulse-dev)

compile:
 $ make
print usage:
 $ ./pacmdvolume
install:
 # make install


== miscellaneous ==

if you have any improvements or suggestions you are welcome to 
implement them and/or contact me


